meta {
  name: GET permissions (v2.10.0 Group B)
  type: http
  seq: 42
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/permissions
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 Group B - Account role + per-permission flags.

  Returns the owner / co-driver role and the individual permission
  list. Surfaced as two diagnostic binary sensors:
  ``permission_is_owner`` (True when the account holds the primary
  owner role) and ``permission_can_command`` (True when the role
  allows remote commands - owner or privileged co-driver).

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Permissions sequence), independently parsed in
  ``seat_cupra.get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape - two variants observed across firmware:
    A) {
         "role": "PRIMARY_USER" | "SECONDARY_USER" | "GUEST",
         "permissions": [
           {"name": "CAN_LOCK", "granted": true},
           {"name": "CAN_UNLOCK", "granted": true},
           ...
         ]
       }
    B) {
         "isOwner": true,
         "canCommand": true,
         ...
       }

  The parser prefers explicit booleans when present and derives both
  flags from ``role`` plus the ``permissions[].name`` membership
  otherwise. Both shapes handled defensively.

  Soft-fails to ``{}`` on 401 / 403 / 404 so older firmware stays
  clean.
}
